# Single source of truth for pinned tool versions consumed by Make,
# lefthook, GitHub Actions workflows, and the dev-environment install
# scripts (initialize.sh, .devcontainer/postCreate.sh).
#
# Format: KEY=VALUE per line, no quotes, no spaces around `=`. Compatible
# with shell `source` and Make `include` directly. For GitHub Actions,
# filter to KEY=VALUE lines first — the $GITHUB_ENV validator rejects
# comments and blank lines:
#   grep -E '^[A-Z_][A-Z0-9_]*=' tool-versions.env >> "$GITHUB_ENV"
#
# Bumping a version: edit the line below, then run `make check-deps` to
# confirm the bump matches what upstream has shipped. CI's
# "Verify workflow tool pins" step asserts that any literal version
# strings in workflow files match what is set here.

SPECTRAL_VERSION=6.16.0
TYPOS_VERSION=v1.47.0
GOSEC_VERSION=v2.27.1
# gocyclo — McCabe cyclomatic complexity reporter for Go. Powers the
# `make complexity-go` target, the `pre-push.complexity` lefthook
# hook, and the CI `complexity` job. REPORT-ONLY: findings are
# printed but never block the build, so the threshold can drift up
# over time without breaking everyone's pushes. The threshold lives
# in the Makefile target (`-over 10` today, per McCabe's original
# paper).
#
# Pinned to `latest` because fzipp/gocyclo hasn't cut a tag in years
# even though main has had drift fixes since. `go install @latest`
# resolves to the current main HEAD; bumping deliberately to a
# specific version once upstream tags again is fine.
GOCYCLO_VERSION=latest
# Semgrep — JS/TS SAST counterpart to gosec. Sweeps the TypeScript
# under frontend/src/ for eval/exec/innerHTML/unsafe-regex patterns
# the ESLint config doesn't cover. Vue SFCs aren't parsed (Semgrep
# has no .vue analyzer); vue/no-v-html in eslint-plugin-vue catches
# the main template-side XSS risk. Bump deliberately — registry
# rulesets (p/javascript, p/typescript, p/owasp-top-ten) are fetched
# at scan time, so even with the pin held the rule set can drift.
SEMGREP_VERSION=1.164.0
HONKIT_VERSION=6.2.1
# Schemathesis — OpenAPI ↔ live-server contract fuzzer. Powers
# `make check-api-drift`, the schemathesis pre-push lefthook hook,
# and the CI schemathesis job. v4 (4.21.0) renamed --base-url → --url
# and --hypothesis-max-examples → --max-examples; OpenAPI 3.1 became
# first-class (no more --experimental flag). If a future bump
# crosses another major boundary, audit scripts/ci/check-api-drift.sh
# and verify with `make check-api-drift` after the install.
SCHEMATHESIS_VERSION=4.21.0
# Tesseract major.minor pin. CI installs `tesseract-ocr=$TESSERACT_VERSION*`
# via apt on Ubuntu so the OCR engine matches what the parser-integration
# goldens (testdata/*.golden.json) were baselined against. macOS dev uses
# whatever Homebrew has; minor patch drift between dev and CI is the
# fragility the pin guards against. Bump when goldens are re-baselined.
TESSERACT_VERSION=5.3.4
